    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_fusco_728961",
        "quote": "In many ways, it's easier to write a book. You have more latitude with structure, and you have the freedom to luxuriate within the internal lives and musings of your characters. But where a screenplay does not always demand great prose, a novel lives or dies by it.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Fusco",
            "url": "/quotes/john_fusco_728961"
